result.execSummary:
The defendant Hou Yang was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Physical Abuse of Child-Intentionally Cause Bodily Harm, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

2:31 PM cases 22CF263, 22CF233, 22CM122 called. Defendant Hou Yang in court.  Attorney Christopher Wilhelm in court for Hou Yang.  Prosecuting attorney Kelly Ronquist in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
State in compliance with victim notification requirements in all three files. There are VIS to be read by the Victim Witness office. Statutory victim P.X. appears via audio only. 
In 22CM122: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1 as charged in the criminal complaint. 
In 22CF263: Defendant pleads No Contest to Counts 2 and 3 as charged in the Information. 
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Court accepts plea and finds defendant Guilty. Anything else is dismissed and read in. 
Victim Witness coordinator Jessica Bryan reads victim impact statements written by F.Y., E.Y. and R.Y. 
State makes an argument for the court to follow the joint agreement. 
State requests the court impose 6 months in jail on Count 2 and 6 months in Jail on count 3 consecutively as part of Probation. 
Defense makes an argument for the Court to follow the joint agreement and asks for 3-4 months of jail. 
Defendant makes a statement before sentencing. 
Court makes a statement regarding the sentencing factors they must consider. 

As to 22CM122: Court orders defendant to pay court costs, including surcharges and provide a DNA sample. 

As to 22CF263 Counts 2 and 3: Court withholds sentencing for 3 years with conditions: 
Defendant to complete parenting classes and follow through with recommendations. 
Defendant to complete domestic abuse assessment and follow through with recommendations. 
Maintain absolute sobriety. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
Defendant not to enter any bars liquor stores or taverns or any place who's primary purpose is the sale of alcohol. 
No contact with P.X. 
No contact with E.Y., F.Y., and R.Y. without their written consent and the consent of the Probation Agent and P.X. 
Complete AODA and follow through with recommendations. 
Defendant to pay court costs including applicable surcharges. 
Defendant to pay restitution $4,460.97 plus applicable surcharges. 
On each count in 22CF263: Court orders 6 months Jail with Huber/Electronic Monitoring if jail deems it appropriate to run consecutively to one another. 
Defendant has 60 days to report.
